# Available Tools

This document describes the tools available to {{.AgentName}}.

Note: Tool availability depends on runtime and configuration.

## File Operations

### read_file
Read the contents of a UTF-8 text file.
```text
read_file(path: string) -> string
```

### write_file
Write content to a UTF-8 text file (creates parent directories if needed).
```text
write_file(path: string, content: string) -> string
```

### edit_file
Edit a file by replacing specific text. `old_text` must appear exactly once.
```text
edit_file(path: string, old_text: string, new_text: string) -> string
```

### list_dir
List directory entries. Returns a JSON array string.
```text
list_dir(path: string, recursive?: bool, maxEntries?: int) -> string
```

## Shell Execution

### exec
Execute a shell command in the workspace directory.
```text
exec(command: string) -> string
```

Safety notes:
- Commands have a timeout (default 60s)
- Dangerous patterns are blocked
- Output is truncated

## Web Access

### web_search
Search the web using Brave Search API. Requires `tools.web.braveApiKey` in config.
```text
web_search(query: string, count?: int) -> string
```

### web_fetch
Fetch a URL and extract readable content. Returns a JSON object string with fields like `status` and `text`.
```text
web_fetch(url: string, extractMode?: "markdown"|"text", maxChars?: int, headers?: {string: string}) -> string
```

Notes:
- HTML extraction is best-effort (not readability)

## Communication

### message
Send a message to a specific channel/chat_id (used internally).
```text
message(content: string, channel: string, chat_id: string) -> string
```

Do NOT use this tool to reply to the current conversation.

## Background Tasks

### spawn
Spawn a subagent to handle a task in the background.
```text
spawn(task: string, label?: string) -> string
```

The result will be reported back asynchronously.

## Scheduled Reminders (Cron)

### cron
Schedule reminders and recurring tasks. Actions: add, list, remove.
```text
cron(action: "add"|"list"|"remove", ...) -> string
```

## Skills

### read_skill
Read a bundled skill (SKILL.md) by name.
```text
read_skill(name: string) -> string
```

